events.description: Athanasius is elected Patriarch of Alexandria.

events.description: Lombard Revolt: Lombard forces led by Melus revolt in Bari against the Byzantine Catepanate of Italy.

events.description: England and Portugal formally ratify their alliance with the signing of the Treaty of Windsor, making it the oldest diplomatic alliance in the world which is still in force.
events.html: • 1386 – England and Portugal formally ratify their alliance with the signing of the Treaty of Windsor, making it the oldest diplomatic alliance in the world which is still in force.

events.description: Timurid monarch 'Abd al-Latif is assassinated.
events.html: • 1450 – Timurid monarch 'Abd al-Latif is assassinated.

events.description: Hernando de Alarcón sets sail on an expedition to the Gulf of California.
events.html: • 1540 – Hernando de Alarcón sets sail on an expedition to the Gulf of California.

events.description: The figure who later became Mr. Punch makes his first recorded appearance in England.
events.html: • 1662 – The figure who later became Mr. Punch makes his first recorded appearance in England.[2]

events.description: Thomas Blood, disguised as a clergyman, attempts to steal England's Crown Jewels from the Tower of London.
events.html: • 1671 – Thomas Blood, disguised as a clergyman, attempts to steal England's Crown Jewels from the Tower of London.

entities.name: Crown Jewels of the United Kingdom

events.description: Five men arrested during a raid on Mother Clap's molly house in London are executed at Tyburn.
events.html: • 1726 – Five men arrested during a raid on Mother Clap's molly house in London are executed at Tyburn.

events.description: Second Schleswig War: The Danish navy defeats the Austrian and Prussian fleets in the Battle of Heligoland.
events.html: • 1864 – Second Schleswig War: The Danish navy defeats the Austrian and Prussian fleets in the Battle of Heligoland.

events.description: American Civil War: Nathan Bedford Forrest surrenders his forces at Gainesville, Alabama.
events.html: • 1865 – American Civil War: Nathan Bedford Forrest surrenders his forces at Gainesville, Alabama.

events.description: American Civil War: President Andrew Johnson issues a proclamation ending belligerent rights of the rebels and enjoining foreign nations to intern or expel Confederate ships.
events.html: • 1865 – American Civil War: President Andrew Johnson issues a proclamation ending belligerent rights of the rebels and enjoining foreign nations to intern or expel Confederate ships.

entities.name: Conclusion of the American Civil War

events.description: Der Krach: The Vienna stock exchange crash heralds the Long Depression.
events.html: • 1873 – Der Krach: The Vienna stock exchange crash heralds the Long Depression.[3]

events.description: Mihail Kogălniceanu reads, in the Chamber of Deputies, the Declaration of Independence of Romania. The date will become recognised as the Independence Day of Romania.
events.html: • 1877 – Mihail Kogălniceanu reads, in the Chamber of Deputies, the Declaration of Independence of Romania. The date will become recognised as the Independence Day of Romania.

events.description: Australia opens its first national parliament in Melbourne.
events.html: • 1901 – Australia opens its first national parliament in Melbourne.

events.description: World War I: Second Battle of Artois between German and French forces.
events.html: • 1915 – World War I: Second Battle of Artois between German and French forces.

events.description: World War I: Germany repels Britain's second attempt to blockade the port of Ostend, Belgium.
events.html: • 1918 – World War I: Germany repels Britain's second attempt to blockade the port of Ostend, Belgium.

events.description: Polish–Soviet War: The Polish army under General Edward Rydz-Śmigły celebrates its capture of Kiev with a victory parade on Khreshchatyk.
events.html: • 1920 – Polish–Soviet War: The Polish army under General Edward Rydz-Śmigły celebrates its capture of Kiev with a victory parade on Khreshchatyk.

events.description: Admiral Richard E. Byrd and Floyd Bennett claim to have flown over the North Pole (later discovery of Byrd's diary appears to cast some doubt on the claim.)
events.html: • 1926 – Admiral Richard E. Byrd and Floyd Bennett claim to have flown over the North Pole (later discovery of Byrd's diary appears to cast some doubt on the claim.)

events.description: The Old Parliament House, Canberra, Australia, officially opens.
events.html: • 1927 – The Old Parliament House, Canberra, Australia, officially opens.[4]

events.description: Italy formally annexes Ethiopia after taking the capital Addis Ababa on May 5.
events.html: • 1936 – Italy formally annexes Ethiopia after taking the capital Addis Ababa on May 5.

events.description: World War II: The German submarine U-110 is captured by the Royal Navy. On board is the latest Enigma machine which Allied cryptographers later use to break coded German messages.
events.html: • 1941 – World War II: The German submarine U-110 is captured by the Royal Navy. On board is the latest Enigma machine which Allied cryptographers later use to break coded German messages.

events.description: The Holocaust in Ukraine: The SS executes 588 Jewish residents of the Podolian town of Zinkiv (Khmelnytska oblast. The Zoludek Ghetto (in Belarus) is destroyed and all its inhabitants executed or deported.
events.html: • 1942 – The Holocaust in Ukraine: The SS executes 588 Jewish residents of the Podolian town of Zinkiv (Khmelnytska oblast. The Zoludek Ghetto (in Belarus) is destroyed and all its inhabitants executed or deported.

events.description: King Victor Emmanuel III of Italy abdicates and is succeeded by Umberto II.

events.description: Czechoslovakia's Ninth-of-May Constitution comes into effect.
events.html: • 1948 – Czechoslovakia's Ninth-of-May Constitution comes into effect.

events.description: Robert Schuman presents the "Schuman Declaration", considered by some to be the beginning of the creation of what is now the European Union.

events.description: Cold War: West Germany joins NATO.

events.description: The Food and Drug Administration announces it will approve birth control as an additional indication for Searle's Enovid, making Enovid the world's first approved oral contraceptive pill.

events.description: Iranian Jewish businessman Habib Elghanian is executed by firing squad in Tehran, prompting the mass exodus of the once 100,000-strong Jewish community of Iran.

events.description: In Florida, United States, Liberian freighter MV Summit Venture collides with the Sunshine Skyway Bridge over Tampa Bay, making a 430-meter (1,400 ft) section of the southbound span collapse. Thirty-five people in six cars and a Greyhound bus fall 46 metres (150 ft) into the water and die.
events.html: • 1980 – In Florida, United States, Liberian freighter MV Summit Venture collides with the Sunshine Skyway Bridge over Tampa Bay, making a 430-meter (1,400 ft) section of the southbound span collapse. Thirty-five people in six cars and a Greyhound bus fall 46 metres (150 ft) into the water and die.

events.description: In Norco, California, United States, five masked gunmen hold up a Security Pacific bank, leading to a violent shoot-out and one of the largest pursuits in California history. Two of the gunmen and one police officer are killed and thirty-three police and civilian vehicles are destroyed in the chase.
events.html: • 1980 – In Norco, California, United States, five masked gunmen hold up a Security Pacific bank, leading to a violent shoot-out and one of the largest pursuits in California history. Two of the gunmen and one police officer are killed and thirty-three police and civilian vehicles are destroyed in the chase.
